Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.29,0:02:13.72,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,The Kingdom of Swaziland, 斯威士兰王国，非洲东南部的内陆国家
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.19,0:00:02.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,本视频由Squarespace赞助
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.19,0:00:02.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This video was made possible by Squarespace
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.62,0:00:06.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,字幕翻译给虫
Dialogue: 2,0:00:02.62,0:00:06.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After this, watch the video I made for their channel More about it after the video
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.05,0:00:13.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,开机场是个很复杂、很有挑战性的事情，很多时候是以盈利为目的的商业活动
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.05,0:00:13.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Airports are incredibly complex and challenging businesses but, in many cases, they’re businesses that make money
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.61,0:00:18.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,很多机场归政府管，但它们仍以商业模式运作——
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.61,0:00:18.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Many airports are owned by governments but still then, they’re often operated as businesses—
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.48,0:00:20.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就和其他公有的商业活动一样
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.48,0:00:20.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,just businesses that are publicly owned
Dialogue: 1,0:00:20.51,0:00:22.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,大多数机场赚钱方式来自于
Dialogue: 2,0:00:20.51,0:00:22.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The majority of airports make their money through
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.57,0:00:26.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,旅客所乘坐的商业航班所使用的机场设施
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.57,0:00:26.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,what they earn from passenger carrying commercial flights using their facilities
Dialogue: 1,0:00:26.51,0:00:30.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一些机场主货运，那钱就都从货运航班里赚来
Dialogue: 2,0:00:26.51,0:00:30.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Some airports are cargo focused and fund their operations through cargo flights
Dialogue: 1,0:00:30.28,0:00:36.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但更多的，你可能也知道，类似希斯罗机场那样，主要是从客运业务中盈利
Dialogue: 2,0:00:30.28,0:00:36.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but the ones that you’ve most heard of, such as London’s Heathrow Airport, rely almost entirely on passenger flights
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.83,0:00:38.86,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而希斯罗机场中的货运业务
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.83,0:00:38.86,1080EN,,0,0,0,,While the amount of cargo going through Heathrow
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.86,0:00:42.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也很大程度上归功于客运旅客的携带行李
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.86,0:00:42.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is significant thanks to passenger aircraft carrying cargo in their holds
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.72,0:00:49.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,纯货运航班的数量只占每日650班中占很小的比值
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.72,0:00:49.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the number of dedicated cargo flights is low in proportion to the airports 650 daily flights
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.21,0:00:54.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们每年从七千八百万客流中赚钱
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.21,0:00:54.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They make their money off of the 78 million passengers flying through each year
Dialogue: 1,0:00:54.24,0:00:58.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,希斯罗机场是世界上最繁忙的纯民营机场——
Dialogue: 2,0:00:54.24,0:00:58.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Heathrow is the busiest airport in the world that is fully privately owned—
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.49,0:01:05.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,英国政府没有其任何股份——所以希思罗机场可以说是机场运营如何盈利的教材
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.49,0:01:05.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the UK government owns no stake in it—and so it is perhaps the best example of an airport built to turn a profit
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.00,0:01:13.05,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每年希斯罗机场运营要花费14亿8565万美元
Dialogue: 2,0:01:06.00,0:01:13.05,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It costs $1,485,650,000 per year to run Heathrow airport
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.26,0:01:19.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这当中包括6500名员工的4亿9400万美元薪水
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.26,0:01:19.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This includes costs like the $494 million Heathrow pays in salaries to its 6,500 employees
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.01,0:01:27.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,现在，有76000人在希斯罗机场工作，但真正为机场工作的只有6500人
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.01,0:01:27.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now, 76,000 people actually work at Heathrow but only those 6,500 actually work for Heathrow
Dialogue: 1,0:01:27.50,0:01:30.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,运营希斯罗机场的公司——希斯罗机场控股
Dialogue: 2,0:01:27.50,0:01:30.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The company that runs Heathrow, Heathrow Airport Holdings
Dialogue: 1,0:01:30.62,0:01:34.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,是唯一真正负责监督并管理机场的部门
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.62,0:01:34.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is only really responsible for the oversight and administration of the airport
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.73,0:01:38.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而在机场内，还有上百个其他公司在运营
Dialogue: 2,0:01:34.73,0:01:38.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Within Heathrow’s walls, though, there are hundreds of other companies operating
Dialogue: 1,0:01:38.70,0:01:44.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其余的七万人分别来自航空公司、行李转运公司、空管公司
Dialogue: 2,0:01:38.70,0:01:44.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Those 70,000 other people work for the airlines, the baggage handling companies, the air traffic control company
Dialogue: 1,0:01:44.60,0:01:50.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,餐馆、租车公司、公交公司还有其他各种在机场工作的雇员
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.60,0:01:50.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the restaurants, the rental car companies, the bus companies, and all the other different employers at the airport
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.27,0:01:53.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,于是当然还会有很多额外的机场运营成本
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.27,0:01:53.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,There are, of course, plenty of other costs involved in running the airport
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.42,0:02:00.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每年2亿3200万的维护、1亿1300万的水费、电费、网费
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.42,0:02:00.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,from the $232 million per year in maintenance to the $113 million yearly utility bill for water, electricity, internet
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.94,0:02:09.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,油气费等，最后总共的15亿，就是每年运营这世界第六繁忙机场的总成本了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.94,0:02:09.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,gas, and more, but overall, that number, $1.5 billion, is what it costs to run the sixth busiest airport in the world
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.29,0:02:13.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这比运营130万人口的斯威士兰王国还要多
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.29,0:02:13.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That’s more than it costs to run the 1.3 million person country of Swaziland
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.85,0:02:15.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以它们怎么赚钱呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:02:13.85,0:02:15.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So how do they pay for that?
Dialogue: 1,0:02:15.82,0:02:20.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,算到每个旅客上，需要每人19美元来运营希思罗机场
Dialogue: 2,0:02:15.82,0:02:20.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On a per passenger basis, it costs $19 to run Heathrow Airport
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.59,0:02:24.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这相当于希斯罗机场要从每位走进机场的旅客身上榨19美元才能自负盈亏
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.59,0:02:24.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Essentially, that means Heathrow needs to make $19 from each passenger
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.59,0:02:27.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这相当于希斯罗机场要从每位走进机场的旅客身上榨19美元才能自负盈亏
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.59,0:02:27.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that passes through its doors in order to break even
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.69,0:02:30.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当然，有些旅客赚得多，有些赚的少
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.69,0:02:30.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Of course, some passengers are more profitable than others
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.81,0:02:36.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到达的旅客通常下了飞机，过海关之后马上就走了，几乎不会买什么东西
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.81,0:02:36.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Arriving passengers generally just get off the plane, go through customs, and leave immediately without buying anything
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.19,0:02:40.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但中转、出发旅客却有很多时间在机场购物
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.19,0:02:40.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,while connecting and departing passengers generally have more time to shop at the airport
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.75,0:02:45.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,零售的利润对任何机场来说都是极为重要的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.75,0:02:45.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Retail is incredibly important to the profitability of any airport
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.07,0:02:48.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这也是为什么机场非常想要尽可能缩短
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.07,0:02:48.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is part of the reason why its in the airports best interest to make
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.22,0:02:53.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,值机和安检的时间——这样旅客才有更多时间购物呀
Dialogue: 2,0:02:48.22,0:02:53.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the check-in and security process as quick as possible—so passengers have more time to shop
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.99,0:02:57.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,希斯罗机场从每一笔零售交易中抽成来赚钱
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.99,0:02:57.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Heathrow makes money through retail by receiving a cut of every sale made
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.98,0:03:04.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,平均下来，机场从餐馆的每位旅客中抽九毛五，从零售商店中每位抽五块一毛五
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.98,0:03:04.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On average, restaurants earn the airport 95 cents per passenger, retail stores earn them $5.15 per passenger
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.84,0:03:07.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,停车场每位抽两块零三分
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.84,0:03:07.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the parking lots add on another $2.03
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.58,0:03:09.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还有其他杂项的收入
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.58,0:03:09.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,then all the other smaller sources of retail revenue
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.93,0:03:14.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,比如租车公司、VIP休息室这些，总共每位旅客抽三块零四分
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.93,0:03:14.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,such as rental car companies and VIP lounges account for another $3.04
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.92,0:03:19.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,希斯罗机场还有个特点是运营一条去伦敦帕丁顿火车站的特快
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.92,0:03:19.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Rather uniquely, Heathrow also operates the express train from the airport to Paddington Station in London
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.06,0:03:22.83,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样每位旅客还能抽两块一毛五
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.06,0:03:22.83,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which makes them another $2.15 per passenger
Dialogue: 1,0:03:23.05,0:03:29.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样，除了机票之外，机场能从每位旅客身上赚十三块三毛二
Dialogue: 2,0:03:23.05,0:03:29.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,All in all, the airport makes $13.32 from passengers through purchases on top of their actual airplane ticket
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.92,0:03:34.86,1080CN,,0,0,0,,需要说明的是，这不是说每位旅客花了十三块三毛二——
Dialogue: 2,0:03:29.92,0:03:34.86,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and its worth pointing out, this doesn’t mean that passengers spend $13.32—
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.04,0:03:38.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这意思是希斯罗机场从每位旅客身上赚取十三块三毛二
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.04,0:03:38.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,this means that Heathrow makes $13.32 per passenger
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.76,0:03:43.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这是机场的抽成——旅客在机场实际花的钱更多
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.76,0:03:43.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is their cut—actual spending at the airport per passenger is much higher
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.77,0:03:49.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,现在你可能会想，这也太黑了吧？没错，的确太贵了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.77,0:03:49.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now, you may think that this amount of retail revenue per passenger is high and you’d be right, it is
Dialogue: 1,0:03:49.25,0:03:54.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,实际上，希斯罗机场是全世界从旅客花销中抽成最高的机场
Dialogue: 2,0:03:49.25,0:03:54.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In fact, it’s one of the highest retail revenues per passenger of any airport worldwide
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.67,0:03:59.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,作为对比，华盛顿杜勒斯机场的值是平均每位旅客五块六毛八
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.67,0:03:59.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In comparison, Washington Dulles Airport makes $5.68 per passenger
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.34,0:04:06.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,奥克兰机场是七块七毛一，巴黎戴高乐机场是十块九毛二
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.34,0:04:06.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Auckland Airport makes $7.71, and Paris Charles de Gaulle Airport makes $10.92 per passenger through retail
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.72,0:04:10.17,1080CN,,0,0,0,,希斯罗机场是让旅客花钱的专家
Dialogue: 2,0:04:06.72,0:04:10.17,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Heathrow is an expert in making passengers spend
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.33,0:04:14.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们绞尽脑汁让旅客花钱
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.33,0:04:14.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They use all sorts of tricks and tactics to increase passenger spending
Dialogue: 1,0:04:14.54,0:04:18.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,比如，三号航站楼，从安检到登机门
Dialogue: 2,0:04:14.54,0:04:18.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,For example, in Terminal 3, to get from security and to the gates
Dialogue: 1,0:04:18.48,0:04:22.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所有旅客都会徒步经过经过免税商店，这大大增加了销售额
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.48,0:04:22.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,all passengers have to walk through duty free which increases sales enormously
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.74,0:04:28.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,希斯罗机场展示板上不显示出发前约45-90分钟的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.74,0:04:28.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Heathrow also doesn’t display the gate for flights until around 45-90 minutes before departure
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.16,0:04:31.39,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这在欧洲的机场很常见，但别的地方却不是
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.16,0:04:31.39,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is common in European airports, but uncommon elsewhere
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.56,0:04:37.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这个设定可以让旅客在飞机起飞前一直在中间有商店、餐馆的地方闲逛
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.56,0:04:37.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Because of this, passengers wait in the central area where shops and restaurants are until just before their flight
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.32,0:04:40.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,使得旅客有更长时间与零售区接触
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.32,0:04:40.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which leads to more time with passengers exposed to the retail environment
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.08,0:04:45.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而作为少有的，可以直飞六大洲的机场
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.08,0:04:45.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Being one of the very few airports with non-stop service to all six inhabited continents
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.40,0:04:49.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,希斯罗有专为长途旅客服务的优势
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.40,0:04:49.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Heathrow also has the advantage of being an airport focused on long-haul service
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.93,0:04:52.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这些航班上的旅客一般很有钱，所以……
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.93,0:04:52.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,These flights tend to carry the wealthiest passengers and...
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.00,0:04:57.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,全世界的旅客平均会在登机前2小时17分到达机场
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.00,0:04:57.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,while worldwide passengers arrive an average of 2 hours and 17 minutes before their flight
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.52,0:05:03.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但希斯罗机场这个时间是2小时51分，说明旅客有更多时间在机场购物
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.52,0:05:03.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Heathrow passengers arrive 2 hours and 51 minutes before which means they have more time to shop at the airport
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.71,0:05:10.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,刚说过，尽管机场要赚19块，但零售只能赚13块
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.71,0:05:10.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As mentioned, though, the airport needs to make $19 per passenger and retail only earns them just over $13
Dialogue: 1,0:05:10.67,0:05:12.83,1080CN,,0,0,0,,剩下的部分就要从航班那里赚了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:10.67,0:05:12.83,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The rest of it comes from flights
Dialogue: 1,0:05:13.00,0:05:18.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每架降落希斯罗机场的飞机平均给机场9500美元
Dialogue: 2,0:05:13.00,0:05:18.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Each plane that lands at Heathrow pays the airport an average of $9,500
Dialogue: 1,0:05:18.51,0:05:20.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当然这和飞机大小有关——
Dialogue: 2,0:05:18.51,0:05:20.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Of course it varies hugely by aircraft—
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.54,0:05:26.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,76座FlyBe航空公司的Dash 8肯定和345座英航747付的钱不一样——
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.54,0:05:26.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a 76 seat FlyBe Dash 8 isn’t paying the same as a 345 seat British Airways 747—
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.17,0:05:29.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但9500美元是这些在希斯罗机场降落的飞机的平均值
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.17,0:05:29.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but $9,500 is the average per visit to Heathrow
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.04,0:05:34.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这些花费有廊桥、值机区、降落次数
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.04,0:05:34.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That goes to pay for things like gate space, a check in area, and the runway time itself
Dialogue: 1,0:05:34.84,0:05:39.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,机场会从飞机降落次数中收费——从小型庞巴迪Dash 8飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:05:34.84,0:05:39.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The airport charges a fixed amount per aircraft landing—for the small Bombardier Dash 8
Dialogue: 1,0:05:39.55,0:05:45.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,价格每次999美元，大到波音747，每次11600美元
Dialogue: 2,0:05:39.55,0:05:45.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it would be $999 while for the large 747 it would be $11,600
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.18,0:05:49.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,对于离港航班，航司要按旅客数量交钱
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.18,0:05:49.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On departure, airlines are then charged again this time per passenger
Dialogue: 1,0:05:49.47,0:05:52.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每位飞往非欧洲地区的旅客
Dialogue: 2,0:05:49.47,0:05:52.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,For each passenger flying to a destination outside of Europe
Dialogue: 1,0:05:52.51,0:05:55.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航司要交58美元
Dialogue: 2,0:05:52.51,0:05:55.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the airline is charged a base of $58
Dialogue: 1,0:05:55.20,0:05:59.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但如果是中转过站旅客，收得会比始发旅客少一点
Dialogue: 2,0:05:55.20,0:05:59.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but this charge is reduced if a passenger connects through Heathrow rather than originating
Dialogue: 1,0:05:59.12,0:06:02.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而远机位也比廊桥便宜
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.12,0:06:02.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,or if the aircraft is parked at a remote stand rather than a gate
Dialogue: 1,0:06:02.54,0:06:08.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,总之，例如满载的76座FlyBe的Dash 8飞国内航线到爱丁堡
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.54,0:06:08.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,All in all, a fully loaded 76 seat FlyBe Dash 8 flying a domestic route to Edinburgh, for example
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.46,0:06:13.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从头到尾大概要交2400美元，从进港、到达、离港
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.46,0:06:13.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,would be charged about $2,400 for its whole visit, arrival and departure
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.20,0:06:20.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而英航747,的747，比如飞纽约，则要交31700美元
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.20,0:06:20.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,while that British Airways 747 flying a long-haul route to New York, for example, would be charged $31,700
Dialogue: 1,0:06:20.20,0:06:23.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,注意这是公开的价格——
Dialogue: 2,0:06:20.20,0:06:23.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It’s worth noting that these are the published prices—
Dialogue: 1,0:06:23.21,0:06:26.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,实际上很多航司的某些飞往希思罗机场的航线
Dialogue: 2,0:06:23.21,0:06:26.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in reality, many airlines with significant numbers of flights at Heathrow
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.75,0:06:29.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会和机场签订一些协议来减少这些开销
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.75,0:06:29.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,have agreements with the airport that reduce their costs
Dialogue: 1,0:06:29.61,0:06:32.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后整理一下，那些数字最后给希斯罗机场
Dialogue: 2,0:06:29.61,0:06:32.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Breaking it down, what those numbers mean is that Heathrow gets
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.59,0:06:36.30,1080CN,,0,0,0,,带来平均每位旅客29美元的利润
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.59,0:06:36.30,1080EN,,0,0,0,,on average, $29 of the cost of every passenger’s ticket
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.48,0:06:41.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以你会发现希斯罗机场赚的还挺多
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.48,0:06:41.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As you can see that means that Heathrow makes a fair bit more than it costs to run the airport
Dialogue: 1,0:06:41.44,0:06:46.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,公司主要用这些钱还之前工程的债务与交税
Dialogue: 2,0:06:41.44,0:06:46.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The company mostly uses this operating profit to pay off debt from prior projects and to pay taxes
Dialogue: 1,0:06:46.32,0:06:51.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以最后，每位旅客真正能赚的钱大约是八块二
Dialogue: 2,0:06:46.32,0:06:51.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so in the end, they’re only truly making about $8.20 off of each of their passengers
Dialogue: 1,0:06:51.58,0:06:57.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而这些数字还告诉我们，希思罗机场是希望有更多远途航班来的
Dialogue: 2,0:06:51.58,0:06:57.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but what these numbers also mean is that, by design, Heathrow is incentivized to attract long-haul flights
Dialogue: 1,0:06:57.74,0:07:00.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,目前机场容量已经饱和
Dialogue: 2,0:06:57.74,0:07:00.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The airport is currently at capacity
Dialogue: 1,0:07:00.14,0:07:05.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们每日最大航班数有657架次，当前是650
Dialogue: 2,0:07:00.14,0:07:05.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Their maximum number of flights per day is 657 and they currently have 650
Dialogue: 1,0:07:05.77,0:07:10.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,真的没有太多油水可以捞了，这意味着唯一增加收入的方法是
Dialogue: 2,0:07:05.77,0:07:10.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They really have no more capacity which means one of the only ways for them to grow financially
Dialogue: 1,0:07:10.84,0:07:12.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,引进大飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:07:10.84,0:07:12.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is to bring in larger planes
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.91,0:07:16.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,76座FlyBe的Dash 8在跑道上呆的时间
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.91,0:07:16.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The 76 seat FlyBe Dash 8 takes up the same time on the runway
Dialogue: 1,0:07:16.73,0:07:20.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,和英航345座747差不多
Dialogue: 2,0:07:16.73,0:07:20.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that could be used by another 345 seat British Airways 747
Dialogue: 1,0:07:20.97,0:07:25.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但让747来却能让机场赚更多的钱
Dialogue: 2,0:07:20.97,0:07:25.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,while the airport would make vastly more money by having that 747 land
Dialogue: 1,0:07:25.35,0:07:31.05,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这也是希斯罗机场飞往英国本土的航班如此至少的原因
Dialogue: 2,0:07:25.35,0:07:31.05,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is no doubt part of the reason why Heathrow is so poorly connected to the country that it’s in—the UK
Dialogue: 1,0:07:31.13,0:07:34.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,整个机场只飞往英国八个机场
Dialogue: 2,0:07:31.13,0:07:34.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The airport only has flights to eight airports in the UK
Dialogue: 1,0:07:34.40,0:07:39.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这数量和希思罗机场飞往中国的城市数量是一样的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:34.40,0:07:39.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which means the airport has exactly the same number of destinations in the UK as it has in China
Dialogue: 1,0:07:39.84,0:07:45.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,作为对比，阿姆斯特丹史基浦机场则可以飞往英国的25个目的地
Dialogue: 2,0:07:39.84,0:07:45.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Amsterdam Airport Schiphol, in the Netherlands, has flights to 25 destinations in the UK
Dialogue: 1,0:07:45.93,0:07:49.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这说明不住在伦敦的英国人
Dialogue: 2,0:07:45.93,0:07:49.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That means that for the vast majority of UK residents living outside of London
Dialogue: 1,0:07:50.01,0:07:55.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,想坐飞机去自己国家的首都，那么在阿姆斯特丹转机更方便
Dialogue: 2,0:07:50.01,0:07:55.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it’s easier to connect to wherever they’re going through Amsterdam than the airport in their capital city
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.40,0:07:58.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,现实就是这样，希斯罗机场是家商业公司
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.40,0:07:58.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The reality is that Heathrow is a commercial company
Dialogue: 1,0:07:58.40,0:08:02.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就算再多的英国人想飞到他们国家最大的机场也没用
Dialogue: 2,0:07:58.40,0:08:02.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,While most UK residents would likely want to see domestic flights to their largest airport
Dialogue: 1,0:08:03.05,0:08:07.17,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而对于希斯罗机场来说，运营短途廉价航班是非常没有商业头脑的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.05,0:08:07.17,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it just doesn’t make commercial sense to operate short and cheap flights to Heathrow
Dialogue: 1,0:08:07.17,0:08:10.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而运营长途航班赚的才多
Dialogue: 2,0:08:07.17,0:08:10.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in the place of highly lucrative long-haul flights
Dialogue: 1,0:08:10.35,0:08:12.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,前者的做法不但机场赚的少
Dialogue: 2,0:08:10.35,0:08:12.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It’s not only less lucrative for the airport
Dialogue: 1,0:08:12.67,0:08:16.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还会让旅客花的更多
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.67,0:08:16.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it’s also more costly for the passenger than flying to other smaller airports
Dialogue: 1,0:08:16.83,0:08:19.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当然，不是每个机场都像希斯罗机场那样
Dialogue: 2,0:08:16.83,0:08:19.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Of course, not every airport is like Heathrow
Dialogue: 1,0:08:19.68,0:08:21.99,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不是每个机场都是商业公司
Dialogue: 2,0:08:19.68,0:08:21.99,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Not every airport is a commercial company
Dialogue: 1,0:08:21.99,0:08:28.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为，很多时候，运营一个机场，公众就没想让它赚钱
Dialogue: 2,0:08:21.99,0:08:28.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That’s just because, in many cases, running an airport the way the public wants it to be run is bad business
Dialogue: 1,0:08:28.54,0:08:32.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,全世界三分之二的机场是赔钱的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:28.54,0:08:32.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,About two thirds of all airports worldwide lose money
Dialogue: 1,0:08:32.56,0:08:37.26,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它们中多数是归政府管，不以赚钱为目的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:32.56,0:08:37.26,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In many cases that’s because they’re government run and just not that focused on making money
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.47,0:08:42.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,美国就不是像英国那种有民营机场的国家
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.47,0:08:42.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The US is a country that has not yet gotten around to airport privatization like the UK
Dialogue: 1,0:08:42.51,0:08:48.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,美国只有一家民营的民航机场——
Dialogue: 2,0:08:42.51,0:08:48.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,There is only one single privately owned and operated airport in the US with commercial passenger flights—
Dialogue: 1,0:08:48.59,0:08:50.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那就是密苏里南部的布兰森机场
Dialogue: 2,0:08:48.59,0:08:50.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that’s Branson Airport in Southern Missouri
Dialogue: 1,0:08:51.04,0:08:55.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,与希斯罗的赚钱不同，布兰森机场在赔钱
Dialogue: 2,0:08:51.04,0:08:55.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Unlike Heathrow, which turns a considerable profit, Branson airport is loosing money
Dialogue: 1,0:08:55.85,0:08:58.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,惨淡经营数年让飞机能飞他们那
Dialogue: 2,0:08:55.85,0:08:58.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and has struggled to keep airlines flying there for more than a few years
Dialogue: 1,0:08:59.05,0:09:02.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,像布兰森机场这种民营的尝试在美国不是第一个——
Dialogue: 2,0:08:59.05,0:09:02.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It’s not like Branson was the only attempt at running a private airport in the US—
Dialogue: 1,0:09:03.00,0:09:05.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,英国的National Express是一家运输公司
Dialogue: 2,0:09:03.00,0:09:05.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,National Express, a UK based transport company
Dialogue: 1,0:09:05.72,0:09:09.39,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在2000年接手了纽约北部60英里的纽堡机场
Dialogue: 2,0:09:05.72,0:09:09.39,1080EN,,0,0,0,,took over Newburgh airport 60 miles north of New York City in 2000
Dialogue: 1,0:09:09.39,0:09:12.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后惨到又把机场卖回了政府
Dialogue: 2,0:09:09.39,0:09:12.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but it too failed and sold the airport back to the government
Dialogue: 1,0:09:12.67,0:09:15.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,美英两国机场民营化的不同在于
Dialogue: 2,0:09:12.67,0:09:15.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The difference between airport privatization in the US and the UK
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.96,0:09:21.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,美国是小机场民营化，英国是大机场民营化
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.96,0:09:21.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is that in the US, the smallest airports went private while in the UK, the largest airports did
Dialogue: 1,0:09:21.63,0:09:26.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在英国，15个最繁忙的机场中10家是民营的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:21.63,0:09:26.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In the UK, ten of the fifteen busiest airports are privately owned and operated
Dialogue: 1,0:09:26.43,0:09:31.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而15个最不繁忙的机场中只有4家是民营的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:26.43,0:09:31.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, only four of the fifteen least busy airports in the country are privately owned
Dialogue: 1,0:09:31.48,0:09:35.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,原因说白了，小机场根本不赚钱
Dialogue: 2,0:09:31.48,0:09:35.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That’s because small airports, in most cases, just don’t make money
Dialogue: 1,0:09:35.85,0:09:39.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而美国的政府运营的不赚钱的小机场
Dialogue: 2,0:09:35.85,0:09:39.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Smaller airports being government run and unprofitable in the US
Dialogue: 1,0:09:39.55,0:09:43.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会给在那里运营的航司某种间接补贴
Dialogue: 2,0:09:39.55,0:09:43.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,allow for a sort of indirect subsidy for airlines to operate there
Dialogue: 1,0:09:43.08,0:09:48.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样一来，机场就会收航司更少的钱来运营
Dialogue: 2,0:09:43.08,0:09:48.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In these cases, airports are willingly charging airlines less than it costs to run the airport to operate there
Dialogue: 1,0:09:48.88,0:09:50.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从而吸引更多航司飞往那里
Dialogue: 2,0:09:48.88,0:09:50.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in order to attract them to fly there
Dialogue: 1,0:09:51.07,0:09:54.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,市级、县级、州政府都愿意这样做
Dialogue: 2,0:09:51.07,0:09:54.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,City, county, or state governments are willing to do this
Dialogue: 1,0:09:54.00,0:09:57.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为他们认为航空业是刺激经济发展的手段
Dialogue: 2,0:09:54.00,0:09:57.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,because they view air service as a stimulant to economic development
Dialogue: 1,0:09:57.61,0:10:00.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,机场运营的公私之争永远不会停止
Dialogue: 2,0:09:57.61,0:10:00.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The merits of private versus public airport ownership can be debated
Dialogue: 1,0:10:00.99,0:10:05.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,支持公有的说机场是基建设施中的必要组成部分
Dialogue: 2,0:10:00.99,0:10:05.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but proponents of publicly owned airports will argue that they’re essential pieces of infrastructure
Dialogue: 1,0:10:05.39,0:10:10.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,支持私有的说私营的便宜服务好
Dialogue: 2,0:10:05.39,0:10:10.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,while those for airport privatization will argue that commercial ownership leads to lower costs and better service
Dialogue: 1,0:10:11.10,0:10:16.19,1080CN,,0,0,0,,即使在英国公众对机场应该公有还是私有的看法也有分歧
Dialogue: 2,0:10:11.10,0:10:16.19,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Even in the UK public opinion is split on whether airports are better off public or private
Dialogue: 1,0:10:16.30,0:10:20.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但重要的是，无论公有还是民营机场，运营都不容易
Dialogue: 2,0:10:16.30,0:10:20.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,What’s sure, though, is that running an airport, whether public or private is not easy
Dialogue: 1,0:10:20.72,0:10:23.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而每天起飞的几百架飞机
